# Sub-projects with their own Vercel projects / deploy targets.
# Keeping them out of the main app's build context avoids accidental
# inclusion in tsconfig walks and shrinks the upload bundle.
#
# docs-site is intentionally NOT excluded here — it has its own Vercel
# project (contentrx-docs) that builds with Root Directory=docs-site,
# and Vercel applies this repo-root .vercelignore to that project too.
# Excluding docs-site here would strip the very files the docs project
# needs to build. Main app is unaffected: tsconfig.json excludes it
# and Next.js routing only looks at src/app/.
cli-client
github-action
mcp-server
.venv

# Claude Code state — settings, worktrees of in-progress work, etc.
# Worktrees in .claude/worktrees/ have their own node_modules and
# Finder-duplicate "node_modules 2" stragglers that surface as build
# warnings on every prod deploy. Nothing in here belongs in the bundle.
.claude
